{"lemma":"أُرْجُوانٌ","slug":"أُرْجُوانٌ","root":"NTWS","root_slug":"NTWS","root_link":"/words/roots/NTWS","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n15004"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8F%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%8F%D9%88%D8%A7%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"redbud (Cercis)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"amethyst"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"the colour purple"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From Aramaic אַרְגְּוָונָא / ܐܰܪܓܽܘܳܢܳܐ (ʾargəwānā), from Akkadian 𒅈𒂵𒌋𒌋𒉡 (argamannu)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n15004","headword_ar":"اُرْجُوَانٌ","root":"rjw","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Redness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain red dye:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain dye, intensely red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) accord. to A'Obeyd, (S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"na$aAsotaj","text_ar":"نَشَاسْتَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, K;) and he says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bahoramaAn","text_ar":"بَهْرَمَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is inferior to it ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwnahu","text_ar":"دُونَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[but this often has the contr. meaning]): it is said also that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArjwAn","text_ar":"ارجوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an arabicized word, from the Pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^arogawaAn","text_ar":"اَرْغَوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":", which means a sort of trees having a red blossom, of the most beautiful kind; and that every colour resembling it is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArjwAn","text_ar":"ارجوان"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Red:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"red garments"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clothes."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAar, K.) And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urojuwaAnN","text_ar":"اُرْجُوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned by Seer has having an intensive meaning; (M, TA;) in the K, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHomaru A^urojuwaAniY~N","text_ar":"اَحْمَرُ اُرْجُوَانِىٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; but this is wrong; (TA;) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Intensely red."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiyfapN HamoraA='u A^urojuwaAnN","text_ar":"قَطِيفَةٌ حَمْرَا=ءُ اُرْجُوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A villous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nappy, outer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wrapping, garment, intensely red"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, M, A:) but IAth says that the most common practice is to prefix the word"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawob","text_ar":"ثَوْب"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiyfap","text_ar":"قَطِيفَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^urojuwaAn","text_ar":"اُرْجُوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"so as to govern the latter in the gen. case; [saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vawobu A^urojuwaAnK","text_ar":"ثَوْبُ اُرْجُوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaTiyfapu A^urojuwaAnK","text_ar":"قَطِيفَةُ اُرْجُوَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":";] and that the word ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ArjwAn","text_ar":"ارجوان"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is said by some to be Arabic, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"n","text_ar":"ن"},{"kind":"text","text":"being augmentative. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","K","S","M","A"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}